Author-Name: Latha Ramchand 
Author-Workplace-Name: College of Business Administration, the University of Houston 
Title: The Impact of Global Equity Offerings 
Abstract:
 This article examines the impact of U.S. firms issuing equity in multiple
 markets. We compare the stock price reactions to announcements of global
 equity offers to a control group of issues offered exclusively in the
 domestic U.S. market. All else equal, the adverse price reaction that
 typically accompanies equity issuance is reduced by 0.8 percent when some
 shares are sold abroad. The overall evidence suggests global offers are
 effective in expanding demand and reducing the price pressure effects
 associated with share issuance. The beneits of global offers appear to be
 associated with an increase in the number of foreign shareholders. Copyright The American Finance Association 2000. 
